A collective sigh of relief was heard throughout the world last night as Rosetta woke from its two-and-half-year slumber.

The probe creaked into action 500 million miles from Earth at 10am yesterday, taking an agonising eight hours to let Earth know that it was ok.  

‘That last quarter of an hour was one of the toughest of my life,’ mission director, Paolo Ferri told MailOnline. ‘I never want to do it again.’

